description: Log coral cover threshold for COTS outbreak (estimated, replaces hard-coded value)
enhanced_semantic_description: Estimated coral cover (%) at which COTS outbreaks are triggered; allows model to flexibly fit outbreak timing and magnitude
ecological_justification: Outbreaks may be triggered at different coral cover levels depending on local conditions; a flexible threshold improves realism and fit.

enhanced_semantic_description: Larval immigration effectiveness in COTS population expansion

description: Log sharpness of outbreak threshold (steepness of sigmoid)
enhanced_semantic_description: Controls how abruptly COTS outbreaks are triggered as coral cover increases; higher values produce more sudden, realistic outbreak onsets
ecological_justification: Observed COTS outbreaks often begin abruptly once coral cover exceeds a critical threshold. A steeper sigmoid better captures this ecological reality and improves model fit to boom-bust cycles.
